***Motor Sub-Assembler***





Whippany Actuation Systems is a dynamic aerospace company that designs and manufactures electromechanical actuators and control electronics for commercial and military applications. Recognized as experts in our industry for over 75 years, we are a fully integrated manufacturing company which takes responsibility for the success of our business and acts quickly to implement new ideas and projects to ensure company growth.





We are looking for a Motor Sub-Assembler to fabricate or assemble mechanical parts, pieces or products using a variety of tools and equipment according to required specifications.





***In this role, you will typically:***


* Assemble, wind, solder, test, and inspect stators, armatures, and components for use in motors and electro-mechanical actuation systems;
* Set-up and operate grinders and balancing machines to rough turn and polish armatures and dynamically balance armatures and motors;
* Perform various production operations including deburring, varnishing, drilling, straightening, lapping and grinding using hand, machine and special tools and mechanical measuring instruments.

***We require:***


* A high school diploma or equivalent;
* One year of experience or equivalent coursework which includes reading and interpreting blue prints and/or schematics or electronics or any combination thereof;
* An ability to wind, or apply varnish, paint and balance rotors and armatures or use a variety or production equipment and machinery;
* Authorization to work in the U.S.

**Eligibility Requirements****:**



This role is restricted to U.S. persons (i.e., U.S. citizens, permanent residents, and other protected individuals under the Immigration and Naturalization Act, 8 U.S.C. 1324b(a)(3)) due to access to export-controlled technology. Whippany Actuation Systems will require proof of status before employment.





***We would really like to see:***


* One year of J STD-001 soldering experience;
* Demonstrated mechanical and electrical ability;
* Ability to use electrical and mechanical measuring instruments and hand tools;
* Strong math skills, good oral and written communication skills, and basic computer skills


For more information and to apply, please visit our website @ www.whipactsys.com/careers


Our Commitment:





Whippany Actuation Systems is an Equal Opportunity / Affirmative Action Employer. We are committed to hiring and retaining a diverse workforce. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.





Individuals who have a disability and would like to request an accommodation with regard to the application and selection process (i.e. the online application or interviews) or have questions regarding our website accessibility, may call 973-560-6662.

