**Unit Clerk Responsibilities**:

* Provides secretarial support to the nursing department/staff as needed, in the areas of medical records, transcription of physician orders and general operation of the unit;
* Experience with medical terminology and transcription is preferred;
* Must demonstrate discretion in handling of confidential information;
* Delivers newadmission chart to unit and initiates forms in preparation for admission;
* Faxes physicians’ orders daily;
* Delivers any faxed printouts to the appropriate department;
* Completes daily transfer of the vital signs and weights from the daily assignment sheet to the resident’s chart;
* Schedules appointments with physicians for the residents; relays the information to nursing;
* Prepares discharge charts for medical records;
* Performs chart audit and report any deficiencies to the Unit Director;
* Maintains medical records per policy;
* Schedules professional agency personnel as directed and supervised by the D.O.N.;
* Keeps unit supplied with necessary forms;
* Orders and charges accordingly, any necessary resident care supplies (i.e., tube feedings, isolation supplies);
* Orders miscellaneous unit stock;
* Completes daily staffing sheets, places in staffing book, and copies these sheets for Unit Director;
* Assists in maintaining staffing needs on unit and making calls to fill staffing needs;
* Refers requests for all information on residents or facility to unit director or nurse coordinator;
* Greets and assists visitors entering unit;
* Answers telephones, directs call and takes messages;
